#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.94"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.94:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:0.2"
msgid "10. Pupphavagga "
msgstr "10. Flowers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 94. Pupphasutta → puppham (or vaddham) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.94:0.3"
msgid "94. Pupphasutta "
msgstr "94. Flowers "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.94:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:1.2"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, lokena vivadāmi, lokova mayā vivadati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I don’t argue with the world; it’s the world that argues with me. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:1.3"
msgid "Na, bhikkhave, dhammavādī kenaci lokasmiṃ vivadati. "
msgstr "When your speech is in line with the teaching you don’t argue with anyone in the world. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:1.4"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, natthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ, ahampi taṃ ‘natthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "What the astute agree on as not existing, I too say does not exist. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:1.5"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, atthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ, ahampi taṃ ‘atthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "What the astute agree on as existing, I too say exists. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.139, sc2
msgctxt "sn22.94:2.1"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, natthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ, yamahaṃ ‘natthī’ti vadāmi? "
msgstr "And what do the astute agree on as not existing, which I too say does not exist? "

msgctxt "sn22.94:2.2"
msgid "Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, niccaṃ dhuvaṃ sassataṃ avipariṇāmadhammaṃ natthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ; ahampi taṃ ‘natthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Form that is permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:2.3"
msgid "Vedanā … "
msgstr "Feeling … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:2.4"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "Perception … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:2.5"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "Choices … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:2.6"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ dhuvaṃ sassataṃ avipariṇāmadhammaṃ natthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ; ahampi taṃ ‘natthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Consciousness that is permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:2.7"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, natthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ; ahampi taṃ ‘natthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is what the astute agree on as not existing, which I too say does not exist. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.94:3.1"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, atthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ, yamahaṃ ‘atthī’ti vadāmi? "
msgstr "And what do the astute agree on as existing, which I too say exists? "

msgctxt "sn22.94:3.2"
msgid "Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ atthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ; ahampi taṃ ‘atthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Form that is impermanent, suffering, and perishable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:3.3"
msgid "Vedanā aniccā … pe … "
msgstr "Feeling … Perception … Choices … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:3.4"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ atthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ; ahampi taṃ ‘atthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Consciousness that is impermanent, suffering, and perishable. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:3.5"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, atthisammataṃ loke paṇḍitānaṃ; ahampi taṃ ‘atthī’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is what the astute agree on as existing, which I too say exists. "

# NOTE: “Temporal” plays on the dual meanings of “worldly” and “temporary”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn22.94:4.1"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, loke lokadhammo, taṃ tathāgato abhisambujjhati abhisameti; "
msgstr "There is a temporal phenomenon in the world that the Realized One understands and comprehends. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:4.2"
msgid "abhisambujjhitvā abhisametvā taṃ ācikkhati deseti paññapeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti. "
msgstr "Then he explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.94:5.1"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, loke lokadhammo, taṃ tathāgato abhisambujjhati abhisameti, abhisambujjhitvā abhisametvā ācikkhati deseti paññapeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti? "
msgstr "And what is that temporal phenomenon in the world? "

msgctxt "sn22.94:5.2"
msgid "Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, loke lokadhammo taṃ tathāgato abhisambujjhati abhisameti. "
msgstr "Form is a temporal phenomenon in the world that the Realized One understands and comprehends. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:5.3"
msgid "Abhisambujjhitvā abhisametvā ācikkhati deseti paññapeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti. "
msgstr "Then he explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.140, sc6
msgctxt "sn22.94:6.1"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, tathāgatena evaṃ ācikkhiyamāne desiyamāne paññapiyamāne paṭṭhapiyamāne vivariyamāne vibhajiyamāne uttānīkariyamāne na jānāti na passati tamahaṃ, bhikkhave, bālaṃ puthujjanaṃ andhaṃ acakkhukaṃ ajānantaṃ apassantaṃ kinti karomi. "
msgstr "This being so, what can I do about a foolish ordinary person, blind and sightless, who does not know or see? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:6.2"
msgid "Vedanā, bhikkhave, loke lokadhammo … pe … "
msgstr "Feeling … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:6.3"
msgid "saññā, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Perception … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:6.4"
msgid "saṅkhārā, bhikkhave … "
msgstr "Choices … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.94:6.5"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ, bhikkhave, loke lokadhammo taṃ tathāgato abhisambujjhati abhisameti. "
msgstr "Consciousness is a temporal phenomenon in the world that the Realized One understands and comprehends. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:6.6"
msgid "Abhisambujjhitvā abhisametvā ācikkhati deseti paññapeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti. "
msgstr "Then he explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn22.94:7.1"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, tathāgatena evaṃ ācikkhiyamāne desiyamāne paññapiyamāne paṭṭhapiyamāne vivariyamāne vibhajiyamāne uttānīkariyamāne na jānāti na passati tamahaṃ, bhikkhave, bālaṃ puthujjanaṃ andhaṃ acakkhukaṃ ajānantaṃ apassantaṃ kinti karomi. "
msgstr "This being so, what can I do about a foolish ordinary person, blind and sightless, who does not know or see? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#. VAR: ṭhāti → tiṭṭhantaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn22.94:8.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, uppalaṃ vā padumaṃ vā puṇḍarīkaṃ vā udake jātaṃ udake saṃvaḍḍhaṃ udakā accuggamma ṭhāti anupalittaṃ udakena; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a blue water lily, or a pink or white lotus. Though it sprouted and grew in the water, it would rise up above the water and stand with no water clinging to it. "

msgctxt "sn22.94:8.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato loke jāto loke saṃvaḍḍho lokaṃ abhibhuyya viharati anupalitto lokenā”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, though I was born and grew up in the world, I live having mastered the world, and the world does not cling to me.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.94:8.3"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
